article.headline: Ivy-Curry scores 20 off the bench, UTSA defeats Tulsa 89-73

article.linkText: Ivy-Curry scores 20 off the bench, UTSA defeats Tulsa 89-73
article.story: SAN ANTONIO -- — Jordan Ivy-Curry's 20 points off of the bench helped UTSA to an 89-73 victory against Tulsa on Wednesday. Ivy-Curry had seven rebounds for the Roadrunners (10-19, 4-12 American Athletic Conference). Chandler Cuthrell added 14 points while going 4 of 9 from the floor, including 4 for 6 from 3-point range, and 2 for 4 from the line, and they also had five rebounds. Christian Tucker and Dre Fuller Jr., both added 12 points. PJ Haggerty led the Golden Hurricane (14-14, 5-11) in scoring, finishing with 29 points and 10 rebounds. Jesaiah McWright added 10 points for Tulsa. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
